&gt; &quot;Dont do anything yet&quot;whispered Hydras then he send an coded message to
&gt; Maxima&quot;My dear MAxima, still there?&quot;

As Hydras attempted to to communicate with the now silent Maxima,
Tankor and his drones led Hydras and his team to the gates of the
mining city. The gates were flanked by several more drones, these
looking like that had some sort of helicoptor altmode, who barely even
glanced at them as they passed by. Overhead twin predacon jets, the
same two that had been circling over the city, took off to make a
wider circle around the city. Meanwhile a dark colored shuttle of some
sort passed over head heading into the city, although what it was was
difficult to make out with the dull haze of smog that blanketed the
city.

&quot;This way.&quot; Tankor said with only the slightest glanced upward at the
sudden spate of airtraffic.

Inside the city it seemed like there were many drones of all different
sorts. most of them looked like drones made from the constructicons:
Dumptrucks, cranes, bulldozers and all sorts made thier way through
the city. The buildings did not seem to be in the best of shape, most
of them covered in dark soot and some sort of brown dust, and while
stable look like they have been barely maintained, some of them had
obviously been abandoned and then pressed into some other service.

Tankor He began leading them towards what was obviously the security
building, and even it seemed like it had once been somethng else, but
now had been pressed into this new service. As they moved several
figures peered out at them from dark alleyways, only thier optics
being dimly seen, but at a glance from Tankor or one of his drones
they fled back into hiding.

&quot;Empties.&quot; Injector said as he walked, his face turned into distaste.
&quot;They were on Cybertron before too. Used up wrecks with no where to
go.&quot;

